With this approach, you can define your data fetching logic in a central location and reuse it across your components. This can help you avoid code duplication and make your code more maintainable.

In addition, React Query also provides a `useQueries` hook that allows you to fetch multiple queries in parallel, which can be useful if you need to fetch multiple pieces of data at the same time.

Overall, while you may still need to use `useQuery` in some places, creating custom hooks and using `useQueries` can help you streamline your data fetching and make your code more maintainable.

